  {name: "12 Hops Of Christmas", description: "12 Hops of Christmas is our is our celebration brew that we concocted with 12 different hops.  This IPA is light in color and dry to the finish.  Celebrate the 12 Days of Christmas with each of theses...Amarillo, Apollo, Bravo, Citra, Centinninal, Calypso, Cascade, Chinook, Nugget, Millenium, Warrior, and Zythos.", abv: "7", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 30, brewery_db_id: "TRptV0"},
  {name: "12 Horse Ale", description: nil, abv: nil, img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 36, brewery_db_id: "eTXOhc"},
  {name: "12 Man", description: nil, abv: "4.5", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 25, brewery_db_id: "SIypH1"},
  {name: "12 Penny Scottish Ale", description: "A Scottish export ale collaboration with Great Fermentations. This cold-conditioned ale puts a light hop on to balance the malt. Add in a nice, crisp finish and you've got a sessionable beer perfect to celebrate Spring, the end of the workday, good friends (consulting 1001 Things to be Happy About)*, peanut butter and jelly sandwiches, puppies, sand dollars...", abv: nil, img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 7, brewery_db_id: "8vtb9K"},
  {name: "120 Minute IPA", description: "Too extreme to be called beer? Brewed to a colossal 45-degree plato, boiled for a full 2 hours while being continuously hopped with high-alpha American hops, then dry-hopped daily in the fermenter for a month & aged for another month on whole-leaf hops!!!\n\nOur 120 Minute I.P.A. is by far the biggest I.P.A. ever brewed! At about 18% abv and 120 ibus you can see why we call this beer THE HOLY GRAIL for hopheads!\n\nWe brew 120 Minute IPA three times a year, but it goes fast. If you find some grab a few bottles, some to enjoy and some to age.", abv: "18", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 31, brewery_db_id: "EWlB8A"},
  {name: "120 Shilling", description: "This strong scotch-style ale has high maltiness, full body, low hop bitterness, flavor & aroma, low-medium fruity esters, very deep copper color,\nslight chill haze, clean alcohol flavor balancing the rich and dominant sweet caramel & dark roasted maltiness flavor and aroma with a very low level of peaty/smoky character from the addition of small amounts of peated malt.", abv: "9.1", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 8, brewery_db_id: "0UUty4"},
  {name: "1225 IPA", description: nil, abv: "5.9", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 30, brewery_db_id: "n1oDDP"},
  {name: "1248 AUGUSTINIAN ALE", description: "Originally brewed to celebrate the 750th anniversary of the Augustinian priory in Clare, Suffolk, birthplace of the Nethergate Brewery. A wonderfully smooth drinking premium beer. A hint of Crystal malt and the late addition of Styrian Goldings hops gives a continental feel. Its habit forming!", abv: "4.5", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 125, brewery_db_id: "xWbsgP"},
  {name: "12th Anniversary Ale", description: "Dry Hopped American Wild Pale Ale", abv: "6", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 25, brewery_db_id: "wZ9yPm"},
  {name: "12th Of Never", description: "Tropically Hoppy. Light, yet Full-Bodied. Bright and Citrusy. Word.\nThe magical, mystical 12th of Never is a blend of Old and New School hops that play bright citrus, rich coconut, and papaya-esque flavors, all on a solid stage of English puffed wheat. Tropically hoppy. Light, yet full-bodied. Bright and citrusy. The 12th of Never Ale is everything we’ve learned about making hop-forward beer expressed in a moderate voice.  Pale, cold, slightly alcoholic and bitter.  It’s all we know.\n\nThese 12oz mini-kegs (AKA cans) are an exciting new option for us, and we are stoopid stoked at the opportunity for y'all to take us to all those new, nelophobic locations…", abv: "5.5", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 25, brewery_db_id: "zfP2fK"},
  {name: "12th Round", description: nil, abv: "7.6", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 37, brewery_db_id: "gSqXk1"},
  {name: "13 Questions", description: nil, abv: "7", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 25, brewery_db_id: "DTNRLo"},
  {name: "13 Rebels ESB", description: "French Broad Brewery’s interpretation of the classic UK Extra Special Bitter. A bright copper color with a complex malt palate is complemented by traditional British hops, notably East Kent Golding. French Broad has made this traditional public house session beer a cult favorite with its skull and crossbones artwork.", abv: "5.2", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 5, brewery_db_id: "FOQMff"},
  {name: "13.Five Ofest", description: "A German-style Oktoberfest Lagerbier. Toasted malt tones with light hopping from the classic German Mittelfrüh variety. The name refers to the German \"Stammwürze” law which states in part that only beer with a minimum of 13.5% Stammwürze (a gravity measurement of wort) is allowed to be served in this Oktoberfest festival. 24 IBUs, 6.0% ABV.", abv: "6", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 102, brewery_db_id: "pACjC4"},
  {name: "1327 Pod's ESB", description: "A well-balanced beer between sweetness from the malt and bitterness from the hops with 5.6% alcohol by volume and 37 IBU. The beer is named after a co-founder of the brewery whose love for the Extra Special Bitter style of beer is why this beer is one of our first releases. The beer is meant to be a little bitter, but not over the top and very drinkable. The hop aroma and flavor do not dominate the beer, but support the malt to create a well balanced beer.", abv: "5.6", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 5, brewery_db_id: "oEUHmS"},
  {name: "1337", description: "Bill + Ron's Excellent Homebrew Ale", abv: "6.3", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 125, brewery_db_id: "m07Muq"},
  {name: "13th Anniversary Ale", description: "Stone 13th Anniversary Ale pours brilliant deep red with a light tan foam. Up front, the aroma is all piney, resinous and citrus hops. Upon tasting, the hops are still on the front, and they are balanced with the malty, toffee like flavors contributed from the blend of crystal and amber malts used in the brewhouse. The finish is deliciously bitter, with a touch of warmth provided by the 9.5% alcohol. Bitterness comes in at 90+ IBU.", abv: "9.5", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 25, brewery_db_id: "todpTX"},
  {name: "142 Blonde Ale with Grits", description: nil, abv: "5.5", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 109, brewery_db_id: "PGxPMn"},
  {name: "1492 IPA", description: "Single-hop IPA showcasing the Columbus hop.", abv: "6", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 30, brewery_db_id: "7Q94GB"},
  {name: "14th Anniversary Ale", description: "For Terrapin’s 14th year anniversary, we thought we would celebrate with a Tart Belgian Red Ale. Brewed with a copious amount of crystal malts for a majestic red color, and fermented with Lactobacillus and a Belgian yeast strain for an acidic and spicy finish, this anniversary ale is one to appreciate all year long.", abv: "7.5", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 70, brewery_db_id: "vysLia"},
  {name: "14° ESB", description: "Our well rounded approach to the classic British Ale. There’s middle of the road, and there’s middle of the river. And if there’s one thing that’s important in the middle of the river – it’s balance.\n\nOur ESB is incredibly well balanced with a slight toasted malt flavor, traditional British hop accents with just a hint of pine and citrus from the unexpected Amarillo / Ahtanum dry-hop.", abv: "5.6", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 5, brewery_db_id: "HAcAaJ"},
  {name: "15 Anniversary", description: nil, abv: "15", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 59, brewery_db_id: "j3eQCh"},
  {name: "1537 Imperial Blonde", description: "Imperial Blonde with a medium/light body offering a light pear aroma. The unique flavor is supported from the caramel notes and finishes with a low floral and mild earthy hop bitterness.", abv: "7.2", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 36, brewery_db_id: "vJbBKT"},
  {name: "1888 Bock", description: "In 1888, After enduring one of the coldest winters on record, the employees of Jacob Leinenkugel's spring brewery crafted their first seasonal beer to celebrate the coming of spring. They blended dark and pale roasted malted barley with select hops and allowed for longer aging to create a robust beer with an exceptionally creamy head. Unchanged since 1888, You'll find our bock's sturdy bod and deep color perfect to draw you out of one season and the into next.", abv: "5.1", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 88, brewery_db_id: "MA2sCi"},
  {name: "Azacca Pale Ale", description: nil, abv: "5.4", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 25, brewery_db_id: "4jpHye"},
  {name: "1554", description: "Born of a flood and centuries-old Belgian text, 1554 Enlightened Black Ale uses a lager yeast strain and dark chocolaty malts to redefine what dark beer can be. In 1997, a Fort Collins flood destroyed the original recipe our researcher, Phil Benstein, found in the library. So Phil and brewmaster, Peter Bouckaert, traveled to Belgium to retrieve this unique style lost to the ages. Their first challenge was deciphering antiquated script and outdated units of measurement, but trial and error (and many months of in-house sampling) culminated in 1554, a highly quaffable dark beer with a moderate body and mouthfeel.", abv: "5.6", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 64, brewery_db_id: "YBW4h3"},
  {name: "15th  Anniversary", description: nil, abv: nil, img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 76, brewery_db_id: "14mWfG"},
  {name: "15th Anniversary Ale", description: "A MAJESTIC ALE FOR A MONUMENTAL OCCASION This noble brew evolved from its common cousins, porter and stout, by necessity to endure the long voyage to the Russian royal court. Colossal additions of American hops are used to balance the robust malt character and infuse this ale with their distinctly citrus-like qualities. 15th Anniversary ale can be consumed now or laid down for later enjoyment. Take some home to share with friends and family at your court.", abv: "9.8", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 43, brewery_db_id: "Jw9k5o"},
  {name: "15th Anniversary Bolt Cutter Barley Wine", description: "Made to Celebrate Founders 15th Anniversary, Bolt Cutter Barley Wine is an American barley wine that pours deep copper color and is strong, sweet and malt-forward, with a spicy complexity. Typical of the style, it is very cellarable. The final product is a blend using beer that was aged in Bourbon barrels, some from aged maple syrup Bourbon barrels and some from standard fermentation. After blending, the beer was allowed to mature in bottles and kegs for a few months before releasing.", abv: "15", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 34, brewery_db_id: "oVesmK"},
  {name: "15th Anniversary Wood Aged Double IPA", description: "Based on our most award-winning beer, Denver Pale Ale, this copper-hued treat is a celebration of everything Great Divide does best. Plenty of malty sweetness provides a backdrop for earthy, floral English and American hops, while French and American oak round off the edges and provide a touch of vanilla. Thanks to everyone who's supported us for the last 15 years—here’s to 15 more!", abv: "10", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 31, brewery_db_id: "YCE6yo"},
  {name: "16 Barrels", description: nil, abv: "10", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 36, brewery_db_id: "EWy8yb"},
  {name: "16 So Fine Red Wheat Wine", description: "For our super heady 16 year anniversary beer we stepped on the gas and headed down the road less traveled! Our b-day present to ourselves was a racy Red Wheat Wine. The brew rips down the road at 11% ABV fueld by a 45% wheat bomb with an after burner hop shot of Amarillo, Willamette, Nelson Sauvignon, and US Goldings that pushes this baby to the limit of sensory overload. Get in. Sit down. Hold on. Shut up.", abv: "11", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 35, brewery_db_id: "UJGpVS"},
  {name: "16-Bit DPA", description: "16-Bit Double Pale Ale is the next generation of pale ale from Tallgrass. For fans of 8-Bit Pale Ale ready to advance to a new realm, 16-Bit DPA is a one-pint finishing move that delivers a sweeping sequence of crisp aromas, light body, bright hoppiness and striking citrus flavors. Best enjoyed in multi-player mode.", abv: "6.2", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 25, brewery_db_id: "Y9mbq2"},
  {name: "1600 Kölsch", description: "FSB’s take on a classic German style beer brewed in honor of the 1600 Group, the community-minded neighbors who united to buy the building that would become Fifth Street Brewpub. They helped make all this possible. It is widely accepted among beer aficionados that the Kölsch was Germany’s answer to the English pale ale. The subtle effervescent fruitiness and mild hop bitterness hovers happily on the palette, and pairs perfectly with fish and light dinners, but just like an IPA or Pilsner, it holds up well with grilled meats and sandwiches. The crisp clean finish makes 1600 Kölsch a naturally great session beer. 1600 Kölsch is incredibly flavorful, and at 5.0% ABV, it’s almost impossible to drink just one.", abv: "5", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 45, brewery_db_id: "HwXClu"},
  {name: "1605 Red", description: "Irish-Style Red Ale brewed with British malts & hops. Perfectly balanced and smooth with subtle notes of caramel and a creamy, full body.\n\nHelp support your community! A portion of proceeds benefits Maryland Firefighters.", abv: "5", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 22, brewery_db_id: "sE49Mg"},
  {name: "1620 IPA", description: "Hazy with a rainbow of hop aromas and flavors, this NE IPA features Mosaic, Citra, Amarillo, and Idaho 7 hops, with a full body that is sure to please.", abv: "6.3", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 30, brewery_db_id: "9216os"},
  {name: "1634 Ale", description: "Originally brewed in 2009, our 1634 Ale was commissioned by Historic Saint Mary’s City to celebrate the 375th anniversary of Maryland’s founding. Lacking any historically documented recipes, our brewers developed the 1634 Ale using malted barley, malted wheat, malted rye, molasses and caraway; ingredients known to be available to brewers in the austere conditions of early Colonial Maryland.", abv: "5.5", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 117, brewery_db_id: "VfUm4r"},
  {name: "1664 Blanc", description: "As a modern, fruity and refreshing beer, Kronenbourg 1664 Blanc appeals to consumers all over the world with its unique taste and appearance.\n \nBrewed with a hint of citrus and coriander spice, Blanc has an inimitable sweet and refreshing flavor that makes it special amongst all the other wheat beers (white beers). It appeals demanding quality seekers.\n \nKronenbourg 1664 Blanc’s modern identity is perfectly expressed by its unique shiny blue bottle.", abv: "5", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 65, brewery_db_id: "wTgdy9"},
  {name: "1687 Brown Ale", description: "Charter Oak's 1687 Brown Ale (this was the year the legend of the Charter Oak took place, and Wadsworth hid the document in the majestic Oak Tree - later to become know as The Charter Oak) is an American style which is slightly more robust than the traditional English Brown Ale. This beer is brewed to a dark copper shade and and well balanced malt and hop with distinctive toasted flavors from both our premium specialty roasted and chocolate malted barley, also allowing for a faint undertone of caramel. This style is lightly hopped for balance and this ale will prove to be a wonderful selection for a sessionable beer. Our medium-bodied, limited bitterness and hop aroma will make this an excellent choice. Look for our 1687 Brown Ale at your favorite watering hole in June.", abv: "5.5", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 12, brewery_db_id: "8zCFMS"},
  {name: "1698", description: "First brewed in 1998 to celebrate Shepherd Neame's tercentenary, this copper-bronze, bottle conditioned beauty is an intense yet uniquely intricate offering thrice-hopped during the brewing process. This adds rich resinous notes and spikes of citrus to a moreish strong ale already rife with notes of liquorice, Masala wine, caramel and spicy orange. A frisson of dark fruit freshens the finish. Serve with smoked cheese.\n \nTasting notes by beer writer Ben McFarland", abv: "6.5", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 138, brewery_db_id: "hvxtKZ"},
  {name: "16th Anniversary Ale", description: nil, abv: nil, img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 125, brewery_db_id: "X1g9H2"},
  {name: "16th Anniversary Stout", description: nil, abv: nil, img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 42, brewery_db_id: "39oXMx"},
  {name: "17", description: "17 is an Imperial Stout brewed with huge amounts of chocolate malts, cacao nibs, and mint leaves. This hearty stout boasts 10% ABV and big chocolate aromas and flavors with a hint of fresh mint. This beer is perfect for the last cold months of the winter. However, it may be enjoyed right away, or allowed to age in the bottle.", abv: "10", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 43, brewery_db_id: "44neoC"},
  {name: "17 Anniversary Götterdämmerung IPA", description: "Our latest anniversary beer, starring an all-German cast of malt and hops, is yet one more glorious example of a Stone IPA brewed outside the box. Our brewers have brought their experiments with German hops to fruition, leaving convention behind to create this hefty IPA entirely with pilsner malts. These provide a superbly crisp mouthfeel, while a unique mix of noble and new-school hop varieties adds layers of bright, bitter flavors. Despite the daunting name, this beer isn't designed to bring about the end of the world, but it just might destroy some of your preconceived notions of what an IPA can be.", abv: "9.5", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 30, brewery_db_id: "w6nBIz"},
  {name: "17-7 Pale Ale", description: "Our hop-forward pale ale named after our address in downtown Two Harbors, 17 – 7th Street.  Brewed with our own 7-hop variety with enough of a biscuit-malt backbone to keep it honest.  Our favorite go-to beer.  5.8% ABV, available year round on tap & in cans", abv: "5.8", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 25, brewery_db_id: "G04CsX"},
  {name: "175", description: nil, abv: "4.2", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 93, brewery_db_id: "e6qtst"},
  {name: "18 Mile Red Grand Cru", description: "18 Mile red is our sour red ale brewed with North Carolina grown heirloom rye malt. This unique regional ale is fermented with a blend of native yeast strains and a pair of traditional  Brettanomyces strains then aged for six months in a collection of regional wine barrels. This rustic refined ale has a bright acidity drawn from a locally collected strain of lactobacillus and is chock full of rich dark fruit notes balanced by an oaky barrel character.", abv: "7.2", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 57, brewery_db_id: "D0Rijr"},
  {name: "18 Mile Rye Pale Ale", description: "We wanted to make rye based beer that highlighted the rye malts unique spicy taste but without the overpowering earthy tones that can come along. We found mashing the base malt at a higher temperature created the perfect balance. We then hopped in with everything under the sun and found our favorite combination came from using predominantly European noble hops that balanced the spiciness from the rye malt and the sweetness from the mashing technique, to make an easy drinking pale ale.", abv: "6", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 117, brewery_db_id: "cG6leo"},
  {name: "1803 Fat Ox Ale", description: "Historically inspired, 1803 Fat Ox Ale is craft-brewed using old wold traditions and ingredients brought to New York by early settlers.  Toasted malt and carmel notes highlight this complex, small batch brew.", abv: nil, img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 13, brewery_db_id: "aeeemz"},
  {name: "1809", description: nil, abv: "5", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 46, brewery_db_id: "vpqpqA"},
  {name: "1811 Lager", description: "Two centuries ago, on the site of what is now the Fort George Brewery block, fur magnate John Jacob Astor’s expedition boldly built a trading post they called Astoria—the first US settlement west of the Rocky Mountains. Today, we’re proud to craft the Official Bicentennial Beer of Astoria.\n Many West Coast brewers in the 19th century had no ice, so they improvised an effervescent beer by brewing lager yeasts at higher-than-normal temperatures. Described as a “refreshing drink, much consumed by the laboring classes,” it’s the inspiration for 1811 lager.\n\nMore flavorful than most modern lagers, and fermented at warmer temperatures, 1811 is lovingly concocted from 2 row malted barley and cracked maize; corn was a popular beer ingredient in pre-Prohibition days. 1811’s hop character gives it a distinctive Northwest style worthy of Astoria’s 200-year history.", abv: "5.1", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 128, brewery_db_id: "9XmyZr"},
  {name: "1812 Amber Ale", description: "Awarded a Silver Medal in the World Beer Championships in the Amber Ale category for 1998, this is our flagship ale. It has a nutty malt flavor which is balanced by a citris hop flavor and a classic ale fruitiness. We distribute this ale on draft and in bottles throughout Northern & Central New York.", abv: "5.2", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 32, brewery_db_id: "kWXWGC"},
  {name: "1814 ESB", description: "After the Battle of Bladensburg the British Army burned Washington to the ground....we ain't bitter! We've realized the best revenge is living well. Please enjoy our British-style session bitter's smooth maltiness and finely balanced hops.", abv: "6.1", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 5, brewery_db_id: "wevPSI"},
  {name: "1819", description: nil, abv: "7.4", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 58, brewery_db_id: "TBNKmt"},
  {name: "1825", description: nil, abv: "9.3", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 63, brewery_db_id: "bpPaLC"},
  {name: "1834 Corktown Rye", description: nil, abv: "6.8", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 117, brewery_db_id: "0tIDxS"},
  {name: "1836", description: "If you ask what 1836 stands for, we'll ask you to put down our beer and leave our country\n\nTexas is more than just tumbleweeds. It’s  shining star, Houston, was founded on the banks of the Buffalo Bayou in 1836. Wild, earthy and soulful, yet balanced in its boldness, 1836 represents a fresh start for beer in Houston.\n\nThis beer combines two of our favorite flavors: a sweet and toasty measure of Victory malts counter-balanced with the earthy, woody, floral aspects of our favorite hops.", abv: "5.7", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 5, brewery_db_id: "SC48ZG"},
  {name: "1842 Czech Pilsener", description: "First brewed in 1842 and taking it's name from the city of Plsen in western Bohemia, pilsener is the original golden lager. The signature taste of Czech Saaz hops compliment pale pilsener malt to create the most famous and beloved styles of Czech beers.", abv: "4", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 76, brewery_db_id: "SJTtiL"},
  {name: "1847 Rye Stout", description: "A dry, bitter, Irish dark ale brewed with malted rye and hopped with Columbus. Extremely dry and roasty. Delicious!", abv: "5", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 42, brewery_db_id: "lTDXBE"},
  {name: "1849", description: "This Ale is truly American. It is a West-Coast original. This style of beer was originally developed in San Francisco, where the air was cool enough to substitute for refrigeration. It is an improvisation of a beer developed as early as the Gold Rush days. One sip, and you'll think you've struck gold!", abv: "5", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 110, brewery_db_id: "mL6yFm"},
  {name: "1854", description: "Where would we be without our home state? Celebrating 165 years of statehood, La Florida officially joined the union in 1845. Hence the name for our All-American Pilsner.\n\nLight in color and balanced in taste, the 1845 deserves it’s own flag. According to the history books, the Governor of Florida signed our statehood papers on the steps of the Capitol. We’re gonna bet the assembled group celebrated with a special kind of Florida beer, if only 1845 had been available on tap!\n\nThe smooth, crisp taste is as American as baseball and apple pie, with a little something special just from Florida thrown in. We might not have a lone star or a tv show about a yankee shoreline, but we do have our own brand of Florida pride. And y’all, we can drink ours.", abv: "4.8", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 98, brewery_db_id: "fzzxsW"},
  {name: "1857", description: "Our master brewer had to brew a tasty lagers. With its very unique bryggkonst he created Disabled 1857, who by chance was a beer in the \"mellanöls\" class.", abv: nil, img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 95, brewery_db_id: "VOzdzW"},
  {name: "1871 Conflagration", description: nil, abv: "7", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 33, brewery_db_id: "J3hNW6"},
  {name: "1887", description: "This Belgian Style Tripel has Spicy notes with a background of supporting bitterness. Earthy flavors and spicy Belgian undertones.", abv: "9.3", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 59, brewery_db_id: "UIyiuZ"},
  {name: "1887", description: "God Created Tangerine", abv: "5", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 119, brewery_db_id: "Xz5UAR"},
  {name: "1887 Red", description: "Well balanced ruby coloured ale with plenty of berry fruit in both taste and aroma.", abv: "4.4", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 32, brewery_db_id: "yJ0hci"},
  {name: "Barrel Aged Vanderbush", description: nil, abv: "9.8", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 59, brewery_db_id: "hayHzd"},
  {name: "1890 Founder's Ale", description: "The Amber Ale, which carries the name 1890 Founder’s Ale, is a tribute to the people who first incorporated Grayton Beach. A classic amber ale - balanced malt and hop character. \n\nThis amber packs a ton of flavor into a small space. A personal favorite.\n- Shank, Head Brewer", abv: "6.1", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 32, brewery_db_id: "k7S5fv"},
  {name: "18th Anniversary", description: "Part of the brewer’s Crown Series, the 18th Anniversary Ale is a double IPA", abv: "10", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 125, brewery_db_id: "yAsuBs"},
  {name: "18th Anniversary Ale", description: "This beer was conceptualized a bit later than usual, and several iterations were created before we settled on this recipe. Using a small amount of English Brown Coffee Malt in a double IPA seemed like an interesting idea to me, and was inspired in part by the success we had brewing Aleman/Two Brothers/Stone DayMan Coffee IPA and The Alchemist/Ninkasi/Stone More Brown Than Black IPA. The malt character is rich and complex, with hints of cocoa and coffee that don't interfere with the hop intensity. We used one of our favorite new hop varieties, El Dorado, 100 percent in the dry-hop stage, which provides a distinctive lemony character in the aroma and taste that we've come to affectionately describe as \"lemon candy.\"", abv: "8", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 30, brewery_db_id: "SR5L1F"},
  {name: "18th Anniversary Belgian Tripel", description: "This brilliant Belgian Tripel showcases the best of our brewers as we bring to life 18 years of passion for beer and strive to crate the most interesting beers possible. This tripel leads with complex citrus aromas that are complimented by a strong undertow of spicy hop character. Ardennes yeast brings forward fruity esters as the Belgian candy sugar added in fermentation softens the body while leading to a vigorous ABV in the finished beer.", abv: "10", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 59, brewery_db_id: "Yd8G8r"},
  {name: "18th Anniversary Wood Aged Double IPA", description: "18th Anniversary Wood Aged Double IPA is a copper-hued treat in celebration of everything Great Divide does best. Plenty of malty sweetness provides a backdrop for earthy, floral English and American hops, while French and American oak round off the edges and provide a touch of vanilla. Thanks to everyone who’s supported us for the last 18 years—here’s to 18 more!", abv: "10", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 31, brewery_db_id: "Mnd972"},
  {name: "19", description: "An IPA with a whopping 19 hop additions.\n\nThe hops and hop percentage in the beer are:\n\nSimcoe 17.14%\nCitra 15.72%\nAmarillo 14.29%\nSorachi Ace 10.71%\nBravo 6.79%\nColombus 6.79%\nCluster 4.64%\nWarrior 4.64%\nCascade 3.57%\nCentennial 3.57%\nPalisade 2.86%\nChallenger 1.43%\nGalena 1.43%\nMagnum 1.43%\nMt. Hood 1.43%\nTettnanger 1.43%\nNugget 0.71%\nSuper Galena 0.71%\nWillamette 0.71%", abv: "6.9", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 30, brewery_db_id: "PIbjTM"},
  {name: "19 - Golden Belgian Style Ale", description: "This Golden Belgian Style Ale matured for over a year on brett in Cabernet and Merlot barrels, then was blended with a bright, citrusy hop-forward Belgian style IPA. Four plus two equals seven here, as the finished product is bigger than the sum of its parts. The art of this crafted cuvee is in the hop profile with a Belgian style nose up front, followed by woody undertones and a complex finish. After 19 years we’re still all about brewing great beer, supporting the communities who drink it and having a kick ass time along the way.", abv: "7", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 135, brewery_db_id: "iJ329Y"},
  {name: "19 Anniversary Thunderstruck IPA", description: "Our 19th anniversary beer brings the boom, delivering it to the palate in a voluminous, hop-driven thunderclap backed by the power of our brewing passion and intensity. This double IPA owes its considerable oomph to a quartet of Australian hops—Topaz and Galaxy, plus newcomers Ella and Vic Secret. We also had Fairview malt shipped in from Australia just for this brew. The beer's striking tropical fruit, citrus and peach hop flavors and slightly resinous and aromatically dank earthiness are sure to electrify your senses.\n\nWe have many special beers planned for release to celebrate our 20 years of brewing, so let this serve as the first course to what will be an undoubtedly epic feast for craft beer enthusiasts, with particular thanks to those who've been with us for the long haul and helped us attain such longevity. Consider this the first of many Thank-Yous...for years to come!", abv: "8.7", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 31, brewery_db_id: "ZQGP3X"},
  {name: "19 Original Colonies", description: "19 Original Colonies Mead is brewed using 5 ingredients: Rogue Hopyard Honey, Wild Flower Honey, Jasmine Silver Tip Green Tea Leaves, Champagne Yeast & Free Range Coastal Water. No Chemicals, additives or preservatives were used.", abv: "5.5", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 148, brewery_db_id: "295GZo"},
  {name: "19-33 Pilsner", description: "A modern golden Pilsner with a smooth, rounded mouthfeel and a hint of light caramel sweetness.  Bright, spicy nose that finishes with a grassy and prickly tart noble hop character from Saaz, Sladek and Hull Melon hops.", abv: "5.4", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 93, brewery_db_id: "2SPG7Z"},
  {name: "1900 Amber Lager", description: "German Melanoiden and Munich malts blend with Willamette hops to create this incredibly refreshing and completely satisfying lager. Bright, refreshing and skillfully balanced — an all purpose après activity brew.", abv: "4.7", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 101, brewery_db_id: "VHOCgc"},
  {name: "1901 Red Ale", description: "This is not your standard Red Ale. This is a very ‘malty’, ‘roasty’ and complex Red Ale. The roasted flavor comes from the high presence of roasted barley. With a very minimal but high alpha hop addition, this Red Ale has become a favorite among patrons.", abv: nil, img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 22, brewery_db_id: "AyZFSh"},
  {name: "1916 Shore Shiver", description: "Man Eating Sharks Infest the Atlantic!\n\nIn the summer of 1916, a shark haunted the New Jersey coastline killing four & injuring seven. While there is much debate over what shark was responsible, there is no question that the attacks found their way into pop books & films  depicting one great white shark who made the shore shiver.", abv: "6.9", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 30, brewery_db_id: "9wNKio"},
  {name: "1919 Root Beer", description: "1919 is brewed in small batches with only the finest ingredients…real granulated sugar ~ the sweetener of choice during the prohibition era ~ and real vanilla. Our unique recipe and these choice ingredients make 1919 the creamiest, full bodied, draft root beer available. In addition, 1919 is alcohol-free and contains no corn syrup, gluten, or caffeine.", abv: nil, img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 139, brewery_db_id: "0DVz81"},
  {name: "1920 Cognac Stout Imperiale", description: "Like the Franco-Belgian Military Accord of 1920, this beer unites a Belgian-style Imperial Stout and one-year aging in a French Cognac oak foudre, coalescing into inviting aromas of dark roast coffee & dark chocolate, cognac, black cherries, wood and hints of molasses, homemade licorice and slight smoke, followed by welcoming favors of espresso roast coffee, prominent dark chocolate & black cherries, plums, French oak tannins and cognac.  Hop bitterness, aromas and flavors are not readily perceived but provide back stage structure to balance the roast malts and oak tannins.  The pleasant, medium body, gentle warming and dry finish of this opaque/black imperial stout perfectly suits it for a snifter on a cold, midwestern night.", abv: "11.64", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 132, brewery_db_id: "YP4dCI"},
  {name: "1927", description: "Juicy. Citrusy. Dank. A tribute to the birth of modern country music. Bristol, Tennessee, 1927.", abv: "7.5", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 29, brewery_db_id: "jT5vQ0"},
  {name: "1945", description: nil, abv: nil, img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 46, brewery_db_id: "22sc9o"},
  {name: "1955 Double Brown", description: nil, abv: "5.1", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 37, brewery_db_id: "wAqRB6"},
  {name: "Brandywine Valley Lager", description: nil, abv: nil, img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 93, brewery_db_id: "3UbArS"},
  {name: "19th Anniversary Ale", description: "A relatively obscure sub-style of porter, this imposing brew honors the roots of its heritage. Like its English counterparts, it is malt forward with the focus on dark malt character. Our porter is a heartier brew like the inspirational beers of the Baltic region. Available for a limited time in 22-oz. bombers and on draught where you can find it", abv: "7.7", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 104, brewery_db_id: "W9GM4Y"},
  {name: "19th Anniversary Ale", description: "To celebrate the brewery’s 19th Anniversary, Great Divide’s brewers deviated from previous years’ anniversary ales and developed an entirely new recipe. The label reads, 19th Anniversary Ale isn’t just a wood-aged ale. It’s a compass – a reminder of where we’ve been and where we’re going. Brewed with pure birch syrup and aged on birch wood, this beer embraces reverential tradition and revolutionary innovation. As we celebrate our 19th year, we hope you’ll join us for the road ahead.", abv: "10.2", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 29, brewery_db_id: "BrAip0"},
  {name: "19th Birthday Suit", description: "In the beginning, cherry trees shaded the beer garden. Resisting temptation no longer, we picked the fruit and let it ferment into a pleasingly sour and subtly sweet ale to mark Uinta’s 19th Birthday. A sinful pleasure for the experienced and adventurous palate.", abv: "7.3", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 119, brewery_db_id: "KYmRUi"},
  {name: "1st Anniversary", description: "Our first year anniversary Imperial Pilsner is an unfiltered, hopped-up lager brewed with true German malt. Hallertau hops, added twice in the fermenter, give this special brew plenty of flavor and aroma while maintaining a drinkable presence. Available on draft and in 22-ounce bottles while supplies last.", abv: "7.4", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 98, brewery_db_id: "kQ42vv"},
  {name: "1st Anniversary Ale", description: nil, abv: "9.3", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 31, brewery_db_id: "lr3HfC"},
  {name: "1st Anniversary Ale", description: "With thanks to our friend Mark Robie, we offer you our first Anniversary beer. Made with uncondensed White Birch sap and our house yeast, its a beer unlike any other. We feel this is the perfect way to show our appreciation to our fans for their continued support of our dream.", abv: "7.6", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 125, brewery_db_id: "EwzrNg"},
  {name: "1st Anniversary Breakers Ball", description: nil, abv: "10.9", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 72, brewery_db_id: "y16meT"},
  {name: "1st Street Ale", description: "This Blonde Ale is dedicated to the city of Katy, Texas. Because Katy was known for its rice farming, we decided to brew this beer with a touch of rice, giving it a smooth, clean, and crisp finish. Perfect for all occasions. Come try it at one of our tasting or look for it at shelf near you.", abv: "5", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 36, brewery_db_id: "myCAim"},
  {name: "1ZENUFF", description: "Another huge IPA knocking you out with a four-hop blend of Apollo, Centennial, Crystal, and Chinook hops. This imperial IPA clocks in at 100 IBUs and 11% ABV, making it just a bit bigger than last fall's Unsessionable, and certainly the kind of beer that you'll need just one of. Toasted malt flavors lurking behind massive levels of hop bitterness and flavor with a punch of of hop aroma reminiscent of fresh citrus rind.", abv: "11", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 31, brewery_db_id: "uV2xqH"},
  {name: "2", description: nil, abv: "7.5", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 41, brewery_db_id: "7D0RRo"},
  {name: "2 Anniversary Ale", description: "Rich mahogany color with ruby highlights, we offer you our second anniversary beer. This oak aged Belgian style dark ale is one to enjoy now, or savor for years to come. We feel this is one small way we can show our appreciation for your continued support of our dream.", abv: "9", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 64, brewery_db_id: "CxBdtx"},
  {name: "2 Biggie", description: nil, abv: "7.1", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 34, brewery_db_id: "MdaCfM"},
  {name: "2 Bit", description: nil, abv: nil, img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 30, brewery_db_id: "dyydfi"},
  {name: "2 Brothers Session IPA", description: "This session IPA is an American Style Pale Ale, Copper in color, mildly malty and packed with citrusy American Cascade hop flavor and aroma.", abv: "4.7", img: nil, avg_score: nil, user_id: nil, brewery_id: nil, availability_id: nil, type_id: 164, brewery_db_id: "HCUkDv"},
